Source-Makefile: feeds/kenzo/luci-app-adguardhome/Makefile
Build-Depends: lua/host luci-base/host LUCI_CSSTIDY:csstidy/host LUCI_SRCDIET:luasrcdiet/host 

Package: luci-app-adguardhome
Submenu: 3. Applications
Version: 1.0-r9
Depends: +libc +ca-certs +curl +wget-ssl +PACKAGE_luci-app-adguardhome_INCLUDE_binary:adguardhome +luci-lua-runtime
Conflicts: 
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Section: luci
Category: LuCI
Repository: base
Title: LuCI app for AdGuardHome
Maintainer: OpenWrt LuCI community
Source: 
URL: https://github.com/openwrt/luci
Type: ipkg
Description:    LuCI support for AdGuardHome
@@
Config:
config PACKAGE_luci-app-adguardhome_INCLUDE_binary
	bool "Include Binary File"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, also pulls in the adguardhome binary package.
	  Disabled by default to avoid init.d/config name conflict with
	  the adguardhome package (uses lowercase init.d/adguardhome,
	  while this LuCI app uses /etc/init.d/AdGuardHome). The LuCI
	  app downloads the binary at runtime, so the package dependency
	  is only needed for offline / sysupgrade scenarios.
@@

Package: luci-app-adguardhome
Submenu: 3. Applications
Version: 1.0-r9
